HER REPORT IS PART OF THE

11:09.569 --> 11:10.637
ENVIRONMENTAL PUBLIC MEDIA

11:10.637 --> 11:12.171
PROJECT EARTHFIX.

11:15.642 --> 11:16.776
>> Reporter: IT'S EARLY MORNING

11:16.776 --> 11:18.611
IN SITKA, ALASKA.

11:18.611 --> 11:19.946
THE STARS HAVE YET TO FADE FROM

11:19.946 --> 11:24.217
THE NIGHT SKY.

11:24.217 --> 11:26.653
A GROUP OF SCIENTISTS IS

11:26.653 --> 11:28.187
SETTING OUT IN SEARCH OF A

11:28.187 --> 11:30.423
DIFFERENT KIND OF STAR.

11:30.423 --> 11:31.824
SEA STARS, COMMONLY KNOWN AS

11:31.824 --> 11:33.459
STARFISH, HAVE BEEN VANISHING

11:33.459 --> 11:35.495
FROM ALASKA'S SHORELINE.

11:35.495 --> 11:36.863
>> Reporter: PETER RAIMONDI IS

11:36.863 --> 11:38.031
ONE OF THE LEAD SCIENTISTS

11:38.031 --> 11:39.465
STUDYING AN ALARMING EPIDEMIC

11:39.465 --> 11:40.800
THAT'S BEEN KILLING STARFISH BY

11:40.800 --> 11:42.335
THE MILLIONS.

11:42.335 --> 11:43.503
>> THESE CRACKS IN THE PREVIOUS

11:43.503 --> 11:44.837
YEARS WOULD HAVE BEEN FULL

11:44.837 --> 11:45.738
THEM.

11:45.738 --> 11:46.940
YOU GUYS DIDN'T GET ANY LAST

11:46.940 --> 11:48.341
TIME, DID YOU?

11:48.341 --> 11:49.442
BACK IN JUNE?

11:49.442 --> 11:50.677
>> Reporter: RAIMONDI AND

11:50.677 --> 11:51.711
RESEARCHER MELISSA MINER HAVE

11:51.711 --> 11:52.679
BEEN CONDUCTING INTENSIVE

11:52.679 --> 11:54.147
SURVEYS OF PACIFIC COASTAL

11:54.147 --> 11:56.149
AREAS, TRACKING THE SPREAD OF

11:56.149 --> 11:58.484
THE DISEASE.

11:58.484 --> 11:59.786
>> ALMOST EVERYWHERE WE'VE

11:59.786 --> 12:01.020
LOOKED IN THE LAST YEAR WE'VE

12:01.020 --> 12:02.622
SEEN CATASTROPHIC LOSSES OF SEA

12:02.622 --> 12:06.693
STARS.

12:06.693 --> 12:07.794
>> Reporter: RAIMONDI POUNDS

12:07.794 --> 12:08.895
BOLTS IN THE ROCKS SO THAT YEAR

12:08.895 --> 12:10.229
AFTER YEAR, THEY CAN FIND AND

12:10.229 --> 12:12.432
SURVEY THE SAME AREAS.

12:12.432 --> 12:13.666
ONCE THEY'VE ROPED OFF A PATCH

12:13.666 --> 12:14.701
OF SHORELINE, THEIR TEAM COUNTS

12:14.701 --> 12:15.702
AND MEASURES THE CREATURES THAT

12:15.702 --> 12:19.339
LIVE HERE.

12:19.339 --> 12:20.974
SITKA WAS ONE OF THE FIRST

12:20.974 --> 12:22.542
PLACES THEY NOTICED SIGNS OF THE

12:22.542 --> 12:26.646
DISEASE LAST YEAR.

12:26.646 --> 12:28.081
NOW THE TEAM IS BACK TO CHECK ON

12:28.081 --> 12:30.249
THE STARS.

12:30.249 --> 12:31.751
THE QUESTION IS, WILL STARFISH

12:31.751 --> 12:33.186
IN THE COOL WATERS OF ALASKA

12:33.186 --> 12:34.988
SURVIVE THIS OUTBREAK?

12:34.988 --> 12:42.228
OR WILL THEY, TOO, SUCCUMB?

12:42.228 --> 12:43.429
>> IT'S DEFINITELY NOT SEVERELY

12:43.429 --> 12:47.033
WASTED, BUT THOSE ARE WHAT WE'RE

12:47.033 --> 12:48.234
CALLING EARLY WARNING SIGNS OF

12:48.234 --> 12:49.802
WASTING.

12:49.802 --> 12:51.104
THIS IS THE BEGINNINGS OF TWO

12:51.104 --> 12:52.372
SEPARATE LESIONS, AND SOMETIMES

12:52.372 --> 12:53.740
WHAT WE SEE IS THAT THIS WILL

12:53.740 --> 12:58.378
GROW TOGETHER AND ACTUALLY, THE

12:58.378 --> 13:00.246
WHOLE TISSUE WILL KIND OF

13:00.246 --> 13:02.115
DEGRADE.

13:02.115 --> 13:03.049
>> Reporter: THE SYMPTOMS VARY

13:03.049 --> 13:04.150
DEPENDING ON THE SPECIES OF

13:04.150 --> 13:06.185
STARFISH, BUT IT USUALLY STARTS

13:06.185 --> 13:07.754
THE SAME WAY.

13:07.754 --> 13:09.355
>> THEY GET WHITE LESIONS.

13:09.355 --> 13:10.523
THEY BECOME NECROTIC, THAT MEANS

13:10.523 --> 13:11.991
THE TISSUE DIES.

13:11.991 --> 13:13.226
AND AS THE TISSUE DIES, THEY

13:13.226 --> 13:14.961
OFTEN TIMES WILL LOSE ARMS AND

13:14.961 --> 13:16.696
THEN WASTE AWAY.

13:16.696 --> 13:18.765
THEY DISINTEGRATE.

13:18.765 --> 13:20.366
>> SOMETIMES THEY GET LESIONS

13:20.366 --> 13:22.001
AND THEIR INTERNAL ORGANS START

13:22.001 --> 13:24.804
TO SPILL OUT OF THESE LESIONS.

13:24.804 --> 13:28.574
AND THAT CAN HAPPEN WITHIN 24 TO

13:28.574 --> 13:31.077
48 HOURS.

13:31.077 --> 13:32.245
>> Reporter: STARFISH DEATHS

13:32.245 --> 13:33.312
WERE FIRST REPORTED IN THE

13:33.312 --> 13:35.415
SUMMER OF 2013 ON WASHINGTON'S

13:35.415 --> 13:37.150
OLYMPIC PENINSULA.

13:37.150 --> 13:38.618
REPORTS HAVE SINCE SURFACED

13:38.618 --> 13:40.286
ALONG THOUSANDS MILES OF NORTH

13:40.286 --> 13:42.255
AMERICA'S PACIFIC SHORES.

13:42.255 --> 13:43.856
SEA STAR WASTING SYNDROME

13:43.856 --> 13:45.525
AFFECTS ALMOST EVERY SPECIES OF

13:45.525 --> 13:47.393
WEST COAST STARFISH.

13:47.393 --> 13:49.095
THE PLAGUE HAS HIT SO HARD OVER

13:49.095 --> 13:51.164
THE PAST YEAR THAT BIOLOGISTS

13:51.164 --> 13:52.465
FEAR THAT SOME SPECIES COULD

13:52.465 --> 13:54.200
EVEN GO EXTINCT.

13:54.200 --> 13:55.635
SCIENTISTS HAVE BEEN SCRAMBLING

13:55.635 --> 14:02.542
TO FIND ANSWERS.

14:02.542 --> 14:03.910
DREW HARVELL IS COORDINATING

14:03.910 --> 14:05.244
NATIONWIDE RESEARCH INTO

14:05.244 --> 14:06.412
UNDERSTANDING THE WASTING

14:06.412 --> 14:08.347
SYNDROME AND HAS BEEN STUDYING

14:08.347 --> 14:11.484
MARINE DISEASES FOR DECADES.

14:11.484 --> 14:13.086
>> THIS IS THE LARGEST DISEASE

14:13.086 --> 14:14.954
OUTBREAK THAT WE KNOW OF EVER IN

14:14.954 --> 14:17.890
THE OCEANS IN TERMS OF THE

14:17.890 --> 14:19.592
NUMBERS OF SPECIES AFFECTED, IN

14:19.592 --> 14:21.160
TERMS OF THE GEOGRAPHIC SCALE,

14:21.160 --> 14:22.662
AND IN TERMS OF THE MORTALITY

14:22.662 --> 14:24.564
THAT'S ASSOCIATED WITH IT.

14:24.564 --> 14:25.765
>> Reporter: AFTER ANALYZING

14:25.765 --> 14:27.100
COUNTLESS SAMPLES IN THE LAB,

14:27.100 --> 14:28.768
HARVELL'S TEAM BELIEVES THAT AN

14:28.768 --> 14:29.969
INFECTIOUS PATHOGEN-- LIKE A

14:29.969 --> 14:32.472
BACTERIA OR VIRUS-- MAY BE THE

14:32.472 --> 14:34.340
ROOT OF THE PROBLEM.

14:34.340 --> 14:35.808
>> THIS IS WHAT WE CALL A WIDE

14:35.808 --> 14:37.477
HOST RANGE PATHOGEN.

14:37.477 --> 14:39.078
IT MEANS THAT IT AFFECTS MANY

14:39.078 --> 14:40.780
DIFFERENT SPECIES.

14:40.780 --> 14:42.615
AND THOSE ARE THE MOST DANGEROUS

14:42.615 --> 14:44.283
IN WILDLIFE DISEASE IN TERMS OF

14:44.283 --> 14:45.718
A POTENTIAL RISK OF EXTINCTION.

14:45.718 --> 14:49.355
>> Reporter: THEY'VE LEARNED THE

14:49.355 --> 14:51.924
SYNDROME SEEMS TO SPREAD THROUGH

14:51.924 --> 14:55.328
WATER AND PHYSICAL CONTACT.

14:55.328 --> 14:57.930
AND THEY'RE TESTING A HYPOTHESIS

14:57.930 --> 15:00.233
THAT THE PATHOGEN MAY BE

15:00.233 --> 15:01.934
TRANSFERRED THROUGH SHELLFISH,

15:01.934 --> 15:03.936
WHICH STARFISH LIKE TO EAT.

15:03.936 --> 15:06.706
EXACTLY WHAT TRIGGERS THESE

15:06.706 --> 15:08.808
OUTBREAKS IS STILL UNKNOWN, BUT

15:08.808 --> 15:11.010
SCIENTISTS THINK THE DISEASE

15:11.010 --> 15:13.279
COULD BE COMPOUNDED BY WARMING

15:13.279 --> 15:15.348
WATERS.

15:15.348 --> 15:18.050
STARFISH ARE STRESSED BY HIGHER

15:18.050 --> 15:19.986
TEMPERATURES, WHICH MAKE THEM

15:19.986 --> 15:21.087
MORE VULNERABLE TO INFECTION.

15:21.087 --> 15:22.288
HARVELL HAS BEEN KEEPING AN EYE

15:22.288 --> 15:23.156
ON THE ONCE ABUNDANT STARFISH

15:23.156 --> 15:24.490
POPULATIONS AROUND WASHINGTON'S

15:24.490 --> 15:25.958
SAN JUAN ISLANDS.

15:25.958 --> 15:27.126
COLD WATER HERE MAY HAVE HELPED

15:27.126 --> 15:28.494
STARFISH WITHSTAND THE FIRST

15:28.494 --> 15:29.695
WAVE OF THE DISEASE.

15:29.695 --> 15:30.897
BUT SUMMERTIME BROUGHT WARMER

15:30.897 --> 15:32.165
WATERS TO THE ISLANDS, AND

15:32.165 --> 15:33.166
HARVELL AND HER TEAM WATCHED

15:33.166 --> 15:33.900
STARS SUDDENLY GET SICK.

15:33.900 --> 15:35.101
>> I'M EXPECTING THAT IN THE

15:35.101 --> 15:36.135
NEXT TWO WEEKS WE WILL LOSE

15:36.135 --> 15:37.336
VIRTUALLY ALL OF THE STARS AT

15:37.336 --> 15:38.437
THIS SITE.

15:38.437 --> 15:39.672
>> Reporter: AND THAT'S EXACTLY

15:39.672 --> 15:40.740
WHAT HAPPENED-- ALL OF THE

15:40.740 --> 15:41.741
STARFISH THAT WERE HERE ARE NOW

15:41.741 --> 15:43.776
GONE.

15:43.776 --> 15:45.211
AS OUTBREAKS CONTINUE IN PUGET

15:45.211 --> 15:46.345
SOUND, SCIENTISTS ARE LOOKING

15:46.345 --> 15:49.315
NORTH FOR A SIGN OF HOPE.

15:49.315 --> 15:51.684
>> THE HOPE IS THAT THE WATERS

15:51.684 --> 15:53.186
ARE COLD ENOUGH IN ALASKA, THE

15:53.186 --> 15:54.687
NORTHERN PART OF THEIR RANGE FOR

15:54.687 --> 15:56.022
MANY OF THESE SPECIES, THAT

15:56.022 --> 15:59.392
THEY'LL PERSIST THERE.

15:59.392 --> 16:01.093
>> Reporter: THIS SUMMER,

16:01.093 --> 16:02.428
MELISSA MINER WAS HOPEFUL THAT

16:02.428 --> 16:04.130
WOULD BE THE CASE.

16:04.130 --> 16:06.265
>> THIS IS ONE OF THE FEW PLACES

16:06.265 --> 16:07.967
THAT COULD POTENTIALLY BE A

16:07.967 --> 16:09.435
SOURCE OF REPLENISHMENT FOR SOME

16:09.435 --> 16:10.770
OF THESE AREAS THAT HAVE BEEN

16:10.770 --> 16:12.438
HIT REALLY HARD.

16:12.438 --> 16:13.906
>> Reporter: BACK IN SITKA,

16:13.906 --> 16:15.174
TROUBLE IS ON THE HORIZON.

16:15.174 --> 16:16.275
IN RECENT MONTHS WATER

16:16.275 --> 16:17.710
TEMPERATURES HERE HAVE BEEN

16:17.710 --> 16:18.911
HIGHER THAN NORMAL, AND THIS

16:18.911 --> 16:20.780
FALL A BAND OF WARM PACIFIC

16:20.780 --> 16:21.948
WATER IS EXPECTED TO TRAVEL

16:21.948 --> 16:23.149
FARTHER NORTH HEATING UP THE

16:23.149 --> 16:24.450
WATERS HERE EVEN MORE.

16:24.450 --> 16:25.885
TO PREPARE, RAIMONDI IS IN

16:25.885 --> 16:27.153
INSTALLING SENSORS WILL MEASURE

16:27.153 --> 16:31.123
THE WATER TEMPERATURE.

16:31.123 --> 16:36.395
>> SO WE'LL GET REALLY GOOD

16:36.395 --> 16:37.830
RECORDS OVER THE NEXT YEAR OF

16:37.830 --> 16:39.632
TEMPERATURE.

16:39.632 --> 16:41.601
THEN WE CAN SEE WHETHER THAT

16:41.601 --> 16:42.935
RELATES TO ANY CHANGE IN THE

16:42.935 --> 16:43.970
DISEASE THAT WE SEE AT THIS

16:43.970 --> 16:49.141
PARTICULAR SITE.

16:49.141 --> 16:50.476
>> Reporter: THAT WAY IF A MASS

16:50.476 --> 16:52.245
DIE-OFF OCCURS, THEY'LL KNOW THE

16:52.245 --> 16:54.580
EXACT OCEAN CONDITIONS.

16:54.580 --> 17:00.086
THERE'S NOTHING THE RESEARCHERS

17:00.086 --> 17:04.223
CAN DO TO PREVENT AN OUTBREAK.

17:04.223 --> 17:05.758
BUT THEY CAN COUNT AND MEASURE

17:05.758 --> 17:07.994
WHAT'S HERE NOW.

17:07.994 --> 17:09.328
THEIR DATA WILL PROVIDE A

17:09.328 --> 17:12.231
CRITICAL POINT OF COMPARISON FOR

17:12.231 --> 17:13.466
WHAT NORMAL STARFISH POPULATIONS

17:13.466 --> 17:14.500
SHOULD BE.

17:14.500 --> 17:15.501
>> IF YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT'S

17:15.501 --> 17:16.736
THERE, YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT'S

17:16.736 --> 17:19.405
LOST.

17:19.405 --> 17:23.109
>> Reporter: THE RESULTS OF THE

17:23.109 --> 17:24.677
ALASKA INTERTIDAL SURVEYS ARE

17:24.677 --> 17:30.149
MIXED.

